<eesti>Tervishoiuteenuste korraldamise seadus </eesti>
<inglise>Health Services Organisation Act </inglise>
<eesti>Vastu v&otilde;etud 9. mail 2001. a. </eesti>
<inglise>Passed 9 May 2001 </inglise>
<eesti>(RT I 2001, 50, 284), </eesti>
<inglise>(RT (1) I 2001, 50, 284), </inglise>
<eesti>j&otilde;ustunud 1. jaanuaril 2002. a. </eesti>
<inglise>entered into force 1 January 2002. </inglise>
<eesti>1. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Seadus s&auml;testab tervishoiuteenuste osutamise korralduse ja n&otilde;uded ning tervishoiu juhtimise, rahastamise ja j&auml;relevalve korra. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Act provides the organisation of and the requirements for the provision of health services, and the procedure for the management, financing and supervision of health care. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Seadust ei kohaldata tervishoiuteenuste osutamise korraldusele kaitsev&auml;es, v&auml;lja arvatud tervishoiut&ouml;&ouml;tajate registreerimise ning ruumide, sisseseade ja aparatuuri j&auml;relevalve osas. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) This Act does not apply to the organisation of the provision of health services in the Defence Forces, except the registration of health care professionals and supervision of facilities, installations and equipment. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>Tervishoiuteenus </eesti>
<inglise>Health services </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tervishoiuteenus on tervishoiut&ouml;&ouml;taja tegevus haiguse, vigastuse v&otilde;i m&uuml;rgituse ennetamiseks, diagnoosimiseks ja ravimiseks eesm&auml;rgiga leevendada inimese vaevusi, hoida &auml;ra tema tervise seisundi halvenemist v&otilde;i haiguse &auml;genemist ning taastada tervist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Health services are the activities of health care professionals for the prevention, diagnosis or treatment of diseases, injuries or intoxication in order to reduce the malaise of persons, prevent the deterioration of their state of health or development of the diseases, and restore their health. </inglise>
<eesti>Tervishoiuteenuste loetelu kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Social Affairs shall establish the list of health services. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Statsionaarne on tervishoiuteenus, mille osutamiseks on vajalik inimese &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evaringne viibimine haiglas. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In-patient health services are health services for the provision of which a person needs to stay at a hospital twenty-four hours a day. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ambulatoorne on tervishoiuteenus, mille osutamiseks inimese &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evaringne viibimine haiglas ei ole vajalik. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Out-patient health services are health services for the provision of which a person does not need to stay at a hospital twenty-four hours a day. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Tervishoiut&ouml;&ouml;taja </eesti>
<inglise>Health care professionals </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tervishoiut&ouml;&ouml;tajad k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on arst, hambaarst, &otilde;de ja &auml;mmaemand, kui nad on registreeritud Tervishoiuametis. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, health care professionals are doctors, dentists, nurses and midwives if they are registered with the Health Care Board. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tervishoiut&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;ib osutada tervishoiuteenuseid omandatud eriala piirides, mille kohta talle on v&auml;ljastatud Tervishoiuameti t&otilde;end tervishoiut&ouml;&ouml;tajana registreerimise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A health care professional may provide health services within the acquired speciality with regard to which the Health Care Board has issued a certificate of registration of the person as an health care professional. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Tervishoiuteenuse osutaja </eesti>
<inglise>Health care providers </inglise>
<eesti>Tervishoiuteenuse osutaja on tervishoiut&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i tervishoiuteenuseid osutav juriidiline isik. </eesti>
<inglise>Health care providers are health care professionals or legal persons providing health services. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Tervishoiuteenuste osutamise korraldus </eesti>
<inglise>Organisation of Provision of Health Services </inglise>
<eesti>1. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 1 </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;ltimatu abi </eesti>
<inglise>Emergency Care </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;ltimatu abi m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of emergency care </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;ltimatu abi k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on tervishoiuteenus, mida tervishoiut&ouml;&ouml;taja osutab olukorras, kus abi edasil&uuml;kkamine v&otilde;i selle andmata j&auml;tmine v&otilde;ib p&otilde;hjustada abivajaja surma v&otilde;i p&uuml;siva tervisekahjustuse. </eesti>
<inglise>For the purposes of this Act, emergency care means health services which are provided by health care professionals in situations where postponement of care or failure to provide care may cause the death or permanent damage to the health of the person requiring care. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;ltimatu abi osutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Provision of emergency care </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Igal Eesti Vabariigi territooriumil viibival inimesel on &otilde;igus saada v&auml;ltimatut abi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Every person in the territory of the Republic of Estonia has the right to receive emergency care. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tervishoiut&ouml;&ouml;taja on kohustatud osutama v&auml;ltimatut abi oma p&auml;devuse ja tema kasutuses olevate v&otilde;imaluste piires. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Health care professionals are required to provide emergency care within the limits of their competence and with the means available. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kohustusliku ravikindlustusega kindlustatud isikule ja temaga v&otilde;rdsustatud isikule (edaspidi ravikindlustusega h&otilde;lmatud isik) osutatud v&auml;ltimatu abi eest tasutakse riigieelarves ravikindlustuseks etten&auml;htud vahenditest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Emergency care provided to persons insured by compulsory health insurance and persons equal thereto (hereinafter persons covered by health insurance) shall be paid for from the funds designated for health insurance in the state budget. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ravikindlustusega h&otilde;lmamata isikule osutatud v&auml;ltimatu abi eest tasutakse riigieelarvest selleks etten&auml;htud vahenditest Sotsiaalministeeriumi ja Eesti Haigekassa vahel s&otilde;lmitud lepingu alusel Eesti Haigekassa poolt vastavalt Eesti Vabariigi ravikindlustusseaduse (RT 1991, 23, 272; RT I 1999, 7, 113; 29, 397; 2000, 57, 374; 84, 536; 102, 675; 2001, 42, 233) &sect; 12 l&otilde;ike 2 alusel Vabariigi Valitsuse kehtestatud tervishoiuteenuste hindade ja nende eest tasumise korrale. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Emergency care provided to persons not covered by health insurance shall be paid for by the Estonian Health Insurance Fund from the funds designated therefor in the state budget on the basis of a contract entered into between the Ministry of Social Affairs and the Estonian Health Insurance Fund pursuant to the prices of health services and the procedure for payment for the health services established by the Government of the Republic pursuant to subsection 12 (2) of the Republic of Estonia Health Insurance Act (RT 1991, 23, 272; RT I 1999, 7, 113; 29, 397; 2000, 57, 374; 84, 536; 102, 675; 2001, 42, 233). </inglise>
<eesti>2. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 2 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ldarstiabi </eesti>
<inglise>General Medical Care </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ldarstiabi m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of general medical care </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;ldarstiabi on ambulatoorne tervishoiuteenus, mida osutavad perearst ja temaga koos t&ouml;&ouml;tavad tervishoiut&ouml;&ouml;tajad. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) General medical care means out-patient health services which are provided by family physicians and health care professionals working together with them. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Perearst on sellekohase eriala omandanud eriarst, kes tegutseb: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A family physician is a specialist who has acquired the corresponding speciality and who practises: </inglise>
<eesti>1) perearsti nimistu alusel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) on the basis of a practice list of the family physician; </inglise>
<eesti>2) nimistuta eriarstina. </eesti>
<inglise>2) as a specialist without a practice list. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 punktis 2 nimetatud perearsti tegevusele kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse haiglav&auml;lise eriarstiabi osutamist reguleerivaid s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The provisions of this Act regulating provision of specialised out-patient care apply to the activities of family physicians specified in clause (2) 2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Perearsti nimistu </eesti>
<inglise>Practice list of family physician </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Perearsti nimistu on k&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel perearsti teenindamisele kuuluvate isikute nimekiri. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The practice list of a family physician is a list of persons who are to be serviced by the family physician pursuant to this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Igal perearstil on &uuml;ks nimistu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Each family physician shall have one practice list. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Igal ravikindlustusega h&otilde;lmatud Eesti kodanikul ja elamisloa alusel Eestis viibival v&auml;lismaalasel on &otilde;igus registreeruda perearsti nimistusse ja vahetada kirjaliku avalduse alusel perearsti. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Every citizen of the Republic of Estonia and alien staying in Estonia on the basis of a residence permit who is covered by health insurance has the right to register in the practice list of a family physician and change a family physician on the basis of a written application. </inglise>
<eesti>Isiku &uuml;leminekut uue perearsti nimistusse arvestatakse j&auml;rgmise kalendrikuu esimesest p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>A person shall be transferred to the practice list of a new family physician as of the first day of the following calendar month. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Perearsti nimistu moodustub perearsti juurde registreerunud isikutest ja maavanema poolt nimistu piirsuurust arvestades alalise elukoha alusel m&auml;&auml;ratud isikutest. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The practice list of a family physician comprises persons registered with the family physician and persons determined by the county governor on the basis of permanent residence, taking into account the maximum number of persons on a practice list. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimistu piirsuuruse, moodustamise, muutmise ja v&otilde;rdlemise alused ning korra kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Social Affairs shall establish the maximum number of persons on practice lists, and the bases of and procedure for the compilation, amendment and comparison of practice lists. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Nimistute piirarvu maakondade kaupa kinnitab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Minister of Social Affairs shall approve the maximum number of practice lists by counties. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Perearst tagab tema nimistusse kantud inimestele tervishoiuteenuste k&auml;ttesaadavuse ning j&auml;rjepidevuse perearsti t&ouml;&ouml;juhendis etten&auml;htud ulatuses ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A family physician shall ensure the accessibility and continuity of health services to persons entered in his or her practice list to the extent and pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the work instructions of family physicians. </inglise>
<eesti>Perearsti t&ouml;&ouml;juhendi kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Social Affairs shall establish the work instructions of family physicians. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Perearst teavitab tema nimistusse kantud inimesi, kuhu ja kelle poole saab isik p&ouml;&ouml;rduda arstiabi saamiseks v&auml;ljaspool perearsti vastuv&otilde;tuaega. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A family physician shall inform persons entered in his or her practice list where and who the persons can turn to in order to receive medical care outside the reception hours of the family physician. </inglise>
<eesti>Eesti Haigekassa v&otilde;ib s&otilde;lmida perearstiga lepingu &uuml;ldarstiabi osutamiseks &otilde;htu- ja &ouml;&ouml;tundidel ning puhkep&auml;evadel. </eesti>
<inglise>The Estonian Health Insurance Fund may enter into a contract with the family physician for the provision of general medical care during evening and night hours and on days off. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Perearsti teeninduspiirkond </eesti>
<inglise>Service area of family physician </inglise>
<eesti>Perearsti teeninduspiirkond on maavanema m&auml;&auml;ratud omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse ala, kus elavale v&otilde;i ajutiselt viibivale isikule, kes ei kuulu perearsti nimistusse, osutab perearst &uuml;ldarstiabi. </eesti>
<inglise>The service area of a family physician is an area of a local government determined by the county governor where the family physician provides general medical care to the persons residing or temporarily staying there who are not included in the practice list of the family physician. </inglise>
<eesti>Perearsti nimistusse mittekuuluvatele isikutele &uuml;ldarstiabi eest tasumise korra kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The procedure for the payment for general medical care to persons not included in the practice list of a family physician shall be established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Perearsti tegevuskoht </eesti>
<inglise>Place of business of family physician </inglise>
<eesti>Perearsti tegevuskoha ruumidele, sisseseadele ja aparatuurile esitatavad n&otilde;uded kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Social Affairs shall establish the requirements for the facilities, installations and equipment of places of business of family physicians. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ldarstiabi rahastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Financing of general medical care </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ravikindlustusega h&otilde;lmatud isikule osutatud &uuml;ldarstiabi eest tasutakse riigieelarves ravikindlustuseks etten&auml;htud vahenditest ulatuses, mille eest tasumise kohustuse on &uuml;le v&otilde;tnud Eesti Haigekassa. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) General medical care provided to persons covered by health insurance shall be paid for from the funds designated for health insurance in the state budget in the amounts in which the Estonian Health Insurance Fund has assumed the obligation to pay for it. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ravikindlustusega h&otilde;lmamata isik tasub &uuml;ldarstiabi eest ise. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Persons not covered by health insurance shall pay for general medical care themselves. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Perearstina tegutsemise &otilde;iguslik vorm </eesti>
<inglise>Legal form of practising as family physician </inglise>
<eesti>Perearstid v&otilde;ivad tegutseda f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjana v&otilde;i asutada &uuml;ldarstiabi osutava &auml;ri&uuml;hingu. </eesti>
<inglise>Family physicians may practise as sole proprietors or found companies providing general medical care. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ldarstiabi osutava &auml;ri&uuml;hingu erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Specifications of companies providing general medical care </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&auml;is&uuml;hingu v&otilde;i usaldus&uuml;hinguna tegutseva &auml;ri&uuml;hingu &uuml;hinguleping s&otilde;lmitakse kirjalikult ja lisatakse &uuml;hingu &auml;riregistrisse kandmise avaldusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The partnership agreement of a company operating as a general partnership or limited partnership shall be entered into in writing and shall be appended to the application for entry of the company in the commercial register. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;ldarstiabi osutav &auml;ri&uuml;hing v&otilde;ib &uuml;hineda ainult teise &uuml;ldarstiabi osutava &auml;ri&uuml;hinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Companies providing general medical care may merge only with other companies providing general medical care. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Uuml;ldarstiabi osutav &auml;ri&uuml;hing ei v&otilde;i olla osanikuks v&otilde;i aktsion&auml;riks eriarstiabi osutavas &auml;ri&uuml;hingus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Companies providing general medical care shall not be partners or shareholders of companies providing specialised medical care. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusala </eesti>
<inglise>Area of activity </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;ldarstiabi osutaval &auml;ri&uuml;hingul ei v&otilde;i olla teist tegevusala peale &uuml;ldarstiabi ja sotsiaalteenuste osutamise ning tervishoiualase &otilde;ppe- ja teadust&ouml;&ouml;. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A company providing general medical care shall not have another area of activity besides providing general medical care and social services, and teaching and scientific research in health care. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) F&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjana &auml;riregistrisse kantud perearst v&otilde;ib &auml;riregistrisse kantud &auml;rinime all osutada ainult &uuml;ldarstiabi, sotsiaalteenuseid ning tegeleda tervishoiualase &otilde;ppe- ja teadust&ouml;&ouml;ga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A family physician entered in the commercial register as sole proprietor may provide only general medical care, social services and engage in teaching and scientific research in health care under the business name entered in the commercial register. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ldarstiabi osutava &auml;ri&uuml;hingu osanik ja aktsion&auml;r </eesti>
<inglise>Partners and shareholders of companies providing general medical care </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;ldarstiabi osutava &auml;ri&uuml;hingu osanik v&otilde;i aktsion&auml;r v&otilde;ib olla &uuml;ksnes selle &uuml;hingu kaudu tervishoiuteenuseid osutav perearst. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Only family physicians providing health services through a company which provides general medical care may be partners and shareholders of the company. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui osanikult v&otilde;i aktsion&auml;rilt on perearstina tegutsemise &otilde;igus &auml;ra v&otilde;etud, peab ta oma osa v&otilde;i aktsia v&otilde;&otilde;randama kolme kuu jooksul perearstile, kes hakkab selle &uuml;hingu kaudu tervishoiuteenuseid osutama. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a partner or shareholder has been deprived of the right to practise as family physician, he or she shall transfer his or her share within three months to a family physician who commences provision of health services through this company. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui osa v&otilde;i aktsiat ei ole kolme kuu jooksul v&otilde;&otilde;randatud, on &auml;ri&uuml;hing kohustatud osa v&otilde;i aktsia t&uuml;histama ja h&uuml;vitama perearstile osa v&otilde;i aktsia v&auml;&auml;rtuse. </eesti>
<inglise>If the share is not transferred within three months, the company is required to cancel the share and compensate the value of the share to the family physician. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud osanik v&otilde;i aktsion&auml;r oli &auml;ri&uuml;hingu ainus osanik v&otilde;i aktsion&auml;r, peab ta oma osa v&otilde;i aktsia v&otilde;&otilde;randama kolme kuu jooksul perearstile, kes hakkab selle &uuml;hingu kaudu tervishoiuteenuseid osutama, v&otilde;i otsustama &auml;ri&uuml;hingu l&otilde;petamise. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the partner or shareholder specified in subsection (2) of this section was the only partner or shareholder of the company, he or she shall transfer the share within three months to a family physician who commences provision of health services through this company, or decide to dissolve the company. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui perearst nimetatud &otilde;igust ei kasuta, l&otilde;petatakse &auml;ri&uuml;hing nimistu moodustamise &otilde;iguse andja n&otilde;udel kohtuotsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>If the family physician does not exercise the specified right, the company shall be dissolved by a court judgment at the request of the person who grants the right to compile practice lists. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Osaniku v&otilde;i aktsion&auml;ri surma korral l&auml;heb &auml;ri&uuml;hingu osa v&otilde;i aktsia &uuml;le tema p&auml;rijale juhul, kui p&auml;rija on perearst ja hakkab osutama selle &uuml;hingu kaudu tervishoiuteenuseid. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In the case of the death of a partner or shareholder, the share of the company shall be transferred to his or her successor if the successor is a family physician who commences provision of health services through this company. </inglise>
<eesti>Muudel juhtudel peab perearsti p&auml;rija v&otilde;&otilde;randama osa v&otilde;i aktsia p&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmisest alates kolme kuu jooksul perearstile, kes hakkab selle &uuml;hingu kaudu tervishoiuteenuseid osutama. </eesti>
<inglise>In other cases, the successor of the family physician shall transfer the share within three months as of acceptance of the succession to a family physician who commences provision of health services through this company. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui osa v&otilde;i aktsia ei ole selle aja jooksul v&otilde;&otilde;randatud, on &auml;ri&uuml;hing kohustatud osa v&otilde;i aktsia t&uuml;histama ja h&uuml;vitama p&auml;rijale osa v&otilde;i aktsia v&auml;&auml;rtuse. </eesti>
<inglise>If the share is not transferred within the period, the company is required to cancel the share and compensate the value of the share to the successor. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 4 nimetatud osanik v&otilde;i aktsion&auml;r oli &auml;ri&uuml;hingu ainus osanik v&otilde;i aktsion&auml;r, v&otilde;ib p&auml;rija p&auml;randi vastuv&otilde;tmisest alates kuue kuu jooksul v&otilde;&otilde;randada osa v&otilde;i aktsia perearstile, kes hakkab selle &uuml;hingu kaudu tervishoiuteenuseid osutama, v&otilde;i otsustada &auml;ri&uuml;hingu l&otilde;petamise. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If the partner or shareholder specified in subsection (4) of this section was the only partner or shareholder of the company, the successor may transfer the share within six months as of acceptance of the succession to a family physician who commences provision of health services through this company, or decide to dissolve the company. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui p&auml;rija ei kasuta nimetatud &otilde;igusi, l&otilde;petatakse &auml;ri&uuml;hing nimistu moodustamise &otilde;iguse andja n&otilde;udel kohtuotsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>If the successor does not exercise the specified rights, the company shall be dissolved by a court judgment at the request of the person who grants the right to compile practice lists. </inglise>
<eesti>3. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Kiirabi </eesti>
<inglise>Emergency Medical Care </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Kiirabi m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of emergency medical care </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kiirabi on ambulatoorne tervishoiuteenus eluohtliku haigestumise, vigastuse v&otilde;i m&uuml;rgituse esmaseks diagnoosimiseks ja raviks ning vajaduse korral abivajaja transpordiks haiglasse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Emergency medical care means out-patient health services for the initial diagnosis and treatment of life-threatening diseases, injuries and intoxication and, if necessary, for the transportation of the person requiring care to a hospital. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;igus saada kiirabiteenust on igal Eesti Vabariigi territooriumil viibival isikul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Each person staying in the territory of the Republic of Estonia has the right to receive emergency medical care. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Kiirabi osutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Provision of emergency medical care </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kiirabi osutab kiirabibrigaad p&auml;&auml;steasutuse h&auml;irekeskuselt saadud v&auml;ljas&otilde;idukorralduse v&otilde;i muul viisil saadud teabe alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An ambulance crew shall provide emergency medical care on the basis of a dispatch order received from the alarm centre of a rescue service agency or information received in any other manner. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vabariigi Valitsus kehtestab kiirabi, haiglate ning p&auml;&auml;ste- ja politseiasutuste kiirabialase koost&ouml;&ouml; korra. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Government of the Republic shall establish the procedure for co-operation in emergency medical care between the emergency medical staff, hospitals, rescue service agencies and police authorities. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Sotsiaalminister kehtestab: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Minister of Social Affairs shall establish: </inglise>
<eesti>1) riigieelarvest rahastatavate avaliku konkursiga valitavate kiirabibrigaadide arvu; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the number of ambulance crews financed from the state budget and selected by way of public competition; </inglise>
<eesti>2) riigieelarvest rahastatavate avaliku konkursita valitavate riigi p&auml;&auml;steasutuste kiirabibrigaadide arvu; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the number of state rescue service agencies and ambulance crews financed from the state budget and selected without public competition; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kiirabibrigaadi t&ouml;&ouml;juhendi; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the work instructions of ambulance crews; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kiirabibrigaadi koosseisule ja varustusele, sealhulgas kiirabiautodele ja meditsiiniseadmetele esitatavad n&otilde;uded; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the requirements for the staff and equipment of ambulance crews, including ambulance cars and medical devices; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kiirabi koost&ouml;&ouml; ja vastastikuse tasaarveldamise korra perearstidega; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the co-operation of emergency medical staff and the procedure for mutual settlement with family physicians; </inglise>
<eesti>6) avaliku konkursi l&auml;biviimise korra kiirabi osutajate valimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the procedure for conducting public competition for selecting the providers of emergency medical care. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tervishoiuamet: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Health Care Board shall: </inglise>
<eesti>1) korraldab sotsiaalministri kehtestatud korras avaliku konkursi riigieelarvest rahastatava kiirabi osutajate valimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) organise a public competition for selecting the providers of emergency medical care financed from the state budget pursuant to the procedure established by the Minister of Social Affairs; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kinnitab riigieelarvest rahastatavate kiirabibrigaadide teeninduspiirkondade arvu ja paiknemise ning kiirabibrigaadide jaotuse teeninduspiirkondade kaupa; </eesti>
<inglise>2) approve the number and location of service areas of ambulance crews financed from the state budget and the distribution of ambulance crews by service areas; </inglise>
<eesti>3) korraldab kiirabibrigaadide ajutist asendamist; </eesti>
<inglise>3) organise the temporary substitution of ambulance crews; </inglise>
<eesti>4) s&otilde;lmib k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktis 1 nimetatud avaliku konkursi v&otilde;itnud kiirabibrigaadi pidajaga kiirabi osutamise lepingu konkursitingimustes m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajaks, kuid mitte kauemaks kui viieks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>4) enter into a contract for the provision of emergency medical care with the owner of the ambulance crew which wins the public competition specified in clause 1) of this subsection by the date designated in the competition conditions, but for not longer than five years. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) P&auml;&auml;steasutuse h&auml;irekeskusel on &otilde;igus suunata kiirabibrigaad abi kohese k&auml;ttesaadavuse tagamiseks teise teeninduspiirkonda. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An alarm centre of a rescue service agency has the right to send ambulance crews to other service areas in order to ensure the immediate accessibility of care. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Riigi p&auml;&auml;steasutuse kiirabibrigaad peab vastama k&auml;esoleva seadusega ja selle alusel kiirabibrigaadile kehtestatavatele n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) An ambulance crew of a state rescue service agency shall comply with the requirements established for ambulance crews by this Act and on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Kiirabi osutamise &otilde;iguslik vorm </eesti>
<inglise>Legal form of provision of emergency medical care </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kiirabibrigaadi pidaja v&otilde;ib olla sellekohase tegevusloaga &auml;ri&uuml;hing, f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja, sihtasutus, riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse p&auml;&auml;steasutus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A company, sole proprietor, foundation or a state or local government rescue service agency which holds a corresponding activity licence may be the owner of an ambulance crew. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kiirabibrigaadi pidaval juriidilisel isikul ei v&otilde;i olla teist tegevusala peale kiirabi osutamise. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A legal person which owns an ambulance crew shall engage in no other area of activity than the provision of emergency medical care. </inglise>
<eesti>Kiirabibrigaadi pidav f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;ib &auml;riregistrisse kantud &auml;rinime all osutada ainult kiirabi. </eesti>
<inglise>A sole proprietor who owns an ambulance crew may provide only emergency medical care under the business name entered in the commercial register. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud tegevusala piirang ei laiene kiirabibrigaadi pidavatele eriarstiabi osutajatele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The restriction on area of activity specified in subsection (2) of this section does not apply to providers of specialised medical care who own an ambulance crew. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tervishoiuamet s&otilde;lmib k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud isikuga lepingu kiirabi osutamiseks sotsiaalministri kehtestatud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Health Care Board shall enter into a contract for the provision of emergency medical care with a person specified in subsection (1) of this section under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Kiirabi rahastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Financing of emergency medical care </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kiirabi eest tasutakse riigieelarvest Sotsiaalministeeriumi kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Emergency medical care shall be paid for from the state budget through the Ministry of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kiirabi rahastamise korra kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Social Affairs shall establish the procedure for the financing of emergency medical care. </inglise>
<eesti>4. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Eriarstiabi </eesti>
<inglise>Specialised Medical Care </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Eriarstiabi m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of specialised medical care </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Eriarstiabi on ambulatoorne v&otilde;i statsionaarne tervishoiuteenus, mida osutavad eriarst v&otilde;i hambaarst ja temaga koos t&ouml;&ouml;tavad tervishoiut&ouml;&ouml;tajad. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Specialised medical care means out-patient or in-patient health services which are provided by specialists or dentists and health care professionals working together with them. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eriarstiabi erialade loetelu kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Social Affairs shall establish the list of specialist fields of specialised medical care. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Haiglav&auml;lise eriarstiabi osutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Provision of specialised out-patient care </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Haiglav&auml;list eriarstiabi v&otilde;ib osutada sellekohase tegevusloaga &auml;ri&uuml;hing v&otilde;i f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Companies or sole proprietors which hold corresponding activity licences may provide specialised out-patient care. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Haiglav&auml;lise eriarstiabi osutamiseks vajalikele ruumidele, sisseseadele ja aparatuurile esitatavad n&otilde;uded kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Social Affairs shall establish the requirements for the facilities, installations and equipment necessary for the provision of specialised out-patient care. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Haigla </eesti>
<inglise>Hospital </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Haigla on ambulatoorsete ja statsionaarsete tervishoiuteenuste osutamiseks moodustatud majandus&uuml;ksus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A hospital is an economic unit formed in order to provide out-patient and in-patient health services. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Haiglat v&otilde;ib pidada sellekohase tegevusloaga aktsiaselts v&otilde;i sihtasutus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A company or foundation which holds a corresponding activity licence may own a hospital. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Haiglat pidaval aktsiaseltsil v&otilde;i sihtasutusel ei v&otilde;i olla teist tegevusala peale eriarstiabi, kiirabi ja sotsiaalteenuste osutamise ning tervishoiualase &otilde;ppe- ja teadust&ouml;&ouml;. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A company or foundation which owns a hospital shall not have another area of activity besides providing specialised medical care, emergency medical care and social services, teaching and scientific research in health care. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Haigla liigid on piirkondlik haigla, keskhaigla, erihaigla, &uuml;ldhaigla, taastusravihaigla ja hooldushaigla. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The types of hospital are: regional hospital, central hospital, special hospital, general hospital, rehabilitation hospital and nursing hospital. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;uded haigla liikidele kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Social Affairs shall establish the requirements for the types of hospital. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Eriarstiabi rahastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Financing of specialised medical care </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ravikindlustusega h&otilde;lmatud isikule osutatud eriarstiabi eest tasutakse riigieelarves ravikindlustuseks etten&auml;htud vahenditest ulatuses, mille eest tasumise kohustuse on &uuml;le v&otilde;tnud Eesti Haigekassa. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Specialised medical care provided to persons covered by health insurance shall be paid for from the funds designated for health insurance in the state budget in the amounts in which the Estonian Health Insurance Fund has assumed the obligation to pay for it. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ravikindlustusega h&otilde;lmamata isik tasub eriarstiabi eest ise. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Persons not covered by health insurance shall pay for specialised medical care themselves. </inglise>
<eesti>5. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 5 </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;endusabi </eesti>
<inglise>Nursing </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;endusabi m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of nursing </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;endusabi on ambulatoorne v&otilde;i statsionaarne tervishoiuteenus, mida osutavad &otilde;de ja &auml;mmaemand koos pere-, eri- v&otilde;i hambaarstiga v&otilde;i iseseisvalt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Nursing means out-patient or in-patient health services which are provided by nurses and midwives together with family physicians, specialists or dentists, or independently. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;endusabi erialade loetelu kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Social Affairs shall establish the list of nursing specialties. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;endusabi iseseisev osutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Independent provision of nursing </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Iseseisvalt v&otilde;ib &otilde;endusabi osutada sellekohase tegevusloaga &auml;ri&uuml;hing v&otilde;i f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Companies or sole proprietors which hold corresponding activity licences may provide nursing independently. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;endusabi iseseisvaks osutamiseks vajalikele ruumidele, sisseseadele ja aparatuurile esitatavad n&otilde;uded kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Social Affairs shall establish the requirements for facilities, installations and equipment necessary for the independent provision of nursing. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Otilde;endusabi tervishoiuteenuste loetelu, mida lubatakse osutada iseseisvalt, kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Minister of Social Affairs shall establish the list of nursing services which are permitted to be provided independently. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Iseseisva &otilde;endusabi rahastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Financing of independent nursing </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ravikindlustusega h&otilde;lmatud isikule osutatud iseseisva &otilde;endusabi eest tasutakse riigieelarves ravikindlustuseks etten&auml;htud vahenditest ulatuses, mille eest tasumise kohustuse on &uuml;le v&otilde;tnud Eesti Haigekassa. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Independent nursing provided to persons covered by health insurance shall be paid for from the funds designated for health insurance in the state budget in the amounts in which the Estonian Health Insurance Fund has assumed the obligation to pay for it. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ravikindlustusega h&otilde;lmamata isik tasub iseseisva &otilde;endusabi eest ise. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Persons not covered by health insurance shall pay for independent nursing themselves. </inglise>
