<eesti>Riigihangete seaduse muutmine </eesti>
<inglise>Amendment of Public Procurement Act </inglise>
<eesti>Riigihangete seaduse (RT I 2000, 84, 534; 2001, 40, 224) &sect; 2 l&otilde;ige 2 muudetakse ja s&otilde;nastatakse j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise>Subsection 2 (2) of the Public Procurement Act (RT I 2000, 84, 534; 2001, 40, 224) is amended and worded as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>"(2) Riigihangeteks ei ole k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 5 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 1 nimetatud ostja ja Eesti Panga poolt asjade ostmine v&otilde;i teenuste tellimine riigiasutuselt, linna- v&otilde;i vallavalitsuselt v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse asutuselt ning Eesti Panga poolt asjade ostmine ja teenuste tellimine Eesti Panga seaduse (RT I 1993, 28, 498; 30, &otilde;iend; 1994, 30, 463; 1998, 64/65, 1006; 1999, 16, 271) &sect;-s 2 nimetatud &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks, samuti Tervishoiuameti poolt kiirabiteenuse ja Eesti Haigekassa poolt raviteenuste, tervise edendamise ja haiguste ennetamise teenuste tellimine, v&auml;lja arvatud ravimite ostmine ning meditsiinitehnika ja nendega seonduvate &otilde;iguste ostmine ja rendile v&otilde;tmine." </eesti>
<inglise>"(2) Purchasing of goods or contracting for services from state agencies, city or rural municipality governments or local government agencies by contracting authorities specified in clause 5 (1) 1) of this Act or the Bank of Estonia, and purchasing of goods or contracting for services by the Bank of Estonia for the performance of the functions specified in &sect; 2 of the Bank of Estonia Act (RT I 1993, 28, 498; 30, correction notice; 1994, 30, 463; 1998, 64/65, 1006; 1999, 16, 271), and contracting for emergency medical care by the Health Care Board, and contracting for health services or health promotion or disease prevention services by the Estonian Health Insurance Fund, except for purchasing of medicinal products or purchasing or commercial lease of medical equipment and related rights, are not deemed to be public procurement." </inglise>
